<HEAD>Council Replaces Out of Date Flag</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KEARNEY, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Old Glory hanging in the City Council
chambers was so old it had only 48 stars.
   Mayor Justus Dobesh said Tuesday he bought a new flag after he
noticed the red, white and blue in the old one had turned gray and
yellow.
   He said it was easier to buy the flag himself than to try
including it in the city's budget.
   ``All the years I've served on the council, I just thought this
was a small contribution I could make,'' said Dobesh, who has been
on the council for 13 years.
   When city officials removed the flag, they found it had only 48
stars, said city finance director Wendell Wessels. But no one knows
when the old flag was bought.
