<DATELINE>RESEARCH TRIANGLE PARK, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Dr. George Hitchings says
he'll donate his share of the 1988 Nobel Prize for medicine to a
foundation he helped create five years ago.
   Hitchings, 83, a scientist emeritus with Burroughs Wellcome Co.,
said Wednesday he would give the $130,000 to the George and Beverly
Hitchings Endowment of the Greater Triangle Community Foundation.
   ``Science, I think, has been pretty well funded,'' Hitchings said
of why he chose charity over scientific projects. ``There are a lot
of people things that are more necessary right now.''
   The foundation makes grants to nearby non-profit agencies.
