<DATELINE>AIKEN, S.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Soul singer James Brown has been indicted in
connection with a police chase that started in Georgia and crossed
into South Carolina.
   Brown was charged Monday with two counts of assault and battery
with intent to kill and one count of failure to stop for a police
car. He earlier was charged in Georgia over the Sept. 24 incident.
   Police said Brown entered a seminar in Augusta carrying a gun,
and then led police on the chase.
   During the chase, Brown allegedly tried to run over two officers
who were setting up a roadblock. The officers shot out Brown's front
tires, and the singer continued driving ``on the rims'' for several
miles before driving his truck into a ditch, according to police
reports.
   Brown, 55, is on a European concert tour, but his attorney has
said he will be back for his trial here next week.
