<HEAD>Officials: Children Witness Mother's Slaying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MENASHA, Wis. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 26-year-old man stabbed his former wife to
death as her three young children who had been awakened by her
screams witnessed the slaying, authorities said.
   Darrel D. Augsburger was being held in lieu of $200,000 bail on a
first-degree murder charge, authorities said.
   A 4-year-old girl and 5-year-old boy watched from the top of a
stairwell early Wednesday as their mother, Deborah Bundy, 25, was
being stabbed at the foot of the stairs by their father, authorities
said.
   Bundy's 8-year-old daughter from another marriage told
authorities of seeing her mother crawling toward the kitchen,
covered with blood. A fourth child who was in the apartment is an
infant.
   Augsburger's two children have been placed temporarily with the
county Department of Social Services, and the other two were staying
with their fathers, said Ann L. Kemmeter, a county social worker.
   ``Under the circumstances, they're doing well, but I don't think
they fully comprehend what's going on,'' she said. ``It's hard
enough for an adult to understand it, let alone children.''
