<HEAD>Books Of `Great One' Donated To Library</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CORAL GABLES, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Comedian Jackie Gleason's collection of
3,700 books _ on topics ranging from UFO's to shooting pool _ has
been donated to the University of Miami library, his widow says.
   Marilyn Gleason says her husband, who died last year, was a
voracious reader who sometimes read a book a day.
   The books reveal that the ``Great One'' had eclectic interests,
including a penchant for the occult and the supernatural.
   Many of the books that piled up at his Lauderhill home dealt with
UFOs, witchcraft and parapsychology. Gleason's reading material also
included autographed road-to-fame autobiographies by fellow
entertainers, history and comedy books, along with tomes on golf and
billards.
   The complete Jackie Gleason library will be housed in the
library's special collections wing.
