<2ND_LINE>PM-Treasury Auction, 1st Ld-Writethru,a0433,000</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Yields Lower on Two-Year Notes</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDs: SUBS 3rd graf, bgng: It was, to CORRECT coupon interest rate</NOTE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on two-year Treasury notes fell in the
latest auction to the lowest level since June.
   The average yield Wednesday was 8.33 percent, down from 8.53
percent at the last auction on Sept. 27.
   It was the lowest rate since two-year notes averaged 8.05 percent
on June 22. The notes will carry a coupon interest rate of 8\
percent, with each $10,000 in face value selling for $9,985.50.
   A total of $9.0 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$25.1 billion.
</TEXT>
