<1ST_LINE>u i PM-Sudan-Terrorists     10-27 0319</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Sudan-Terrorists,0331</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Five Palestinians Condemned For Terrorist Attacks</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MOHAMED OSMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KHARTOUM, Sudan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five Palestinians shouted ``Revolution
Until Victory'' today after they were sentenced to hang for
terrorist attacks that killed five Britons and two Sudanese.
   Judge Ahmed Bashir pronounced the five guilty of murder in the
bombing of a hotel and a gun attack on a social club, both of which
occurred in May.
   The attacks also injured 20 people, including three Americans.
The five British deaths included a family of four.
   No date was set for the five to hang. Jalal Aly Lutfy, the chief
defense lawyer, said he would file an appeal within the required 40
days.
   Court records identified the Palestinians as Imad Ahmed Huello,
Hassan Gasim Nimir, Sharif Ismat Atwa, Mustafa Arif and Ibrahim Ali.
   The sentencing hearing had been postponed four times.
   After the third postponement Oct. 17, the United States expressed
concern over reports in Khartoum that Abu Nidal, a Palestinian
terrorist whose group has been linked to many terror attacks, was
trying to buy lenient treatment for the accused in exchange for
money to help flood victims.
   Sudanese security sources said in May that two of the convicted
men told investigators they were members of Abu Nidal's group.
   The sources quoted the two men as saying the attacks were meant
to avenge the assassination of Khalil Wazir, or Abu Jihad, a close
adviser to Palestine Liberation Organization leader Yasser Arafat.
Wazir was killed at his home earlier this year in Tunis, the capital
of Tunisia, by commandos which Arab and other sources linked to
Israeli intelligence.
   However, Prime Minister Sadek Mahdi of Sudan issued a statement
Wednesday saying he believed the five have no connection with
Palestinian organizations.
   ``This is because the only profiting side from such acts which
were committed by the said element is the Zionist entity,'' or
Israel, he said without elaborating.
</TEXT>
