<HEAD>One-Time Hahn Minister Indicted On Tax Evasion Charge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A minister who was once Jessica Hahn's boss
was indicted today on charges he skimmed funds from his Long Island
church and then tried to persude Ms. Hahn to lie to a grand jury
about it.
   The Rev. Eugene Profeta, 51, was charged by an Albany County
grand jury of tax evasion, perjury and tampering with a witness. He
pleaded innocent and was being held pending $25,000 bail.
