<HEAD>President Tries Hog Call</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LITTLE ROCK, Ark. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan mixed politicking with
a little hog calling during a campaign stop here Friday on behalf of
Republican presidential candidate George Bush.
   Winding up a speech at Adams Field here, the president was
presented with an enlargement of a popular Arkansas bumper sticker
reading, ``I'm a Bush hog.''
   After explaining to those in the audience who couldn't see it
what the sticker said, Reagan shouted out: ``Hey pig, sooie!''
   Well, almost.
   The Arkansas Razorbacks' yell is ``Woo pig, sooie.''
</TEXT>
