<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Reagan recommended Thursday that the
new U.S. Embassy in Moscow be razed and rebuilt from the ground up
because it is riddled with listening devices that cannot be removed.
   Reagan told reporters the United States has ``no choice'' in the
matter ``because there's no way to rid it of the many listening
devices that were built into it.''
   ``We're going to start and have an American-built one,'' Reagan
said of the embassy.
