<HEAD>Reports Record Sales for First Fiscal Quarter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sara Lee Corp. said Thursday its first fiscal
quarter profit climbed 22 percent on a 14.6 percent revenue rise,
saying sales were especially strong in its food-services and
packaged consumer products businesses.
   Sara Lee said its net income for the quarter that ended Oct. 1
rose to $75.6 million, or 65 cents per share, from $61.9 million, or
54 cents a share, reported for the same period last year.
   First-quarter sales rose to $2.8 billion from last year's $2.4
billion.
   Packaged foods, the company's largest business segment, reported
$1.2 billion in sales for the quarter, up 8.3 percent from $1.1
billion a year ago.
   The Sara Lee Bakery segment of its packaged foods division posted
a 9 percent unit volume gain, enjoying particularly strong sales in
its international and bakery and delicatessan operations, the
company said.
   Sara Lee's food-service division reported first-quarter sales of
$653.8 million, up 16 percent from $563.7 million a year earlier.
   First-quarter sales for Sara Lee's packaged consumer products,
including Hanes hosiery, climbed 22.4 percent to $853.5 million from
$697.5 million last year.
</TEXT>
