<HEAD>Stocks Mixed</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Shares prices finished mixed Thursday on the London
Stock Exchange as the government reported better-than-expected
British trade figures.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index rose 1.4
points, or 0.08 percent, to 1,852.1.
   But the narrower Financial Times 30-share index closed down 0.6
point at 1,502.6. And the Financial Times 500-share index was up
1.28 at 1,053.48.
   Trading activity was brisk throughout the day, as a total of
581.5 million shares changed hands, compared with the 481.3 million
shares Wednesday.
   Prices rallied after the late-morning release of the British
trade report for September.
   The merchandise trade deficit narrowed to 1.06 billion pounds, or
$1.87 billion, last month from 1.81 billion pounds, or $3.19
billion, in August, the Department of Trade and Industry said.
   The financial markets had expected the deficit to widen slightly.
   But later, prices fell back as the Dow Jones industrial average
sank about 30 points lower in the first hour of trading in New York.
   By the close of London trading, the Dow Jones average was off
35.02 points.
