<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Wheat futures prices were mixed while corn and
soybeans fell Thursday in trading at the Chicago Board of Trade.
   An announcement from the U.S. Agriculture Department that China
is being offered 550,000 tons of wheat under the export bonus plan
sparked buying in the wheat pit, analysts said.
   But the slide of corn and soybean prices confirmed sentiment that
