<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-Pennzoil     10-27 0342</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-Pennzoil,0355</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Posats Big Profit Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pennzoil Co. said Thursday its earnings soared
eightfold in the third quarter as the company continued to benefit
from a record cash settlement of its litigation with Texaco Inc.
   Pennzoil said all segments of its Houston-based energy company
contributed toward the improved profits, with increased earnings in
the oil and gas, sulphur and refinery operations.
   For the third quarter, after-tax profits totaled $39.8 million,
or 93 cents per share, compared with $4.7 million, or 2 cents per
share, a year earlier.
   Third-quarter revenue rose 37.1 percent to $617 million from $450
million in the July-September quarter of 1987.
   Profits for the first nine months of 1988 were $1.4 billion, or
$36 per share, on revenues of $1.65 billion, compared with $26
million, or 35 cents per share, on revenues of $1.34 billion during
the same 1987 period.
   Earnings for the nine-month period of 1988 include a $1.7 billion
extraordinary gain, or $41.83 per share, associated with the $3
billion cash settlement with Texaco.
   Earlier this year, Pennzoil agreed to accept the settlement from
Texaco to resolve an $11.1 billion court judgment won by Pennzoil
against its oil company rival in a 1985 Texas trial. In that case, a
jury found Texaco had interfered with Pennzoil's plan to buy Getty
Oil Co.
   In the most recent quarter, Pennzoil also showed after-tax
non-cash charges of $303 million, or $7.65 per share, resulting from
the disposition and write-down of certain assets and other charges.
   Third-quarter earnings improved dramatically because of
investment income and increased operating income in all divisions,
including $5.1 million from Facet Enterprises Inc., a filtration
products company acquired in May 1988.
   Investment income in the third quarter was $53.3 million,
compared with $11.2 million in the third quarter of 1987, the
company said.
   Operating income from oil and gas production was $7.1 million in
the third quarter, compared with the same 1987 period and petroleum
products showed a gain of $33 million in the quarter, compared with
$30 million a year earlier.
</TEXT>
